[1853.900053, "o", "\u001b[12;1H\u001b[13;1H\u001b[7m-----Info: (grep)Introduction, 17 lines --60%-------------------------------\u001b[0m\u001b[1;1H**************\u001b[2;1H\u001b[K\u001b[3;1HGiven one or more patterns, ‘grep’ searches input files for matches to\u001b[4;1Hthe patterns.  When it finds a match in a line, it copies the line to\u001b[K\u001b[5;1Hstandard output (by default), or produces whatever other sort of output\u001b[6;1Hyou have requested with options.\u001b[K\u001b[7;1H\u001b[K\u001b[8;1H   Though ‘grep’ expects to do the matching on text, it has no limits on\u001b[9;1Hinput line length other than available memory, and it can match\u001b[K\u001b[10;1Harbitrary characters within a line.  If the final byte of an input file\u001b[11;1His not a newline, ‘grep’ silently supplies one.  Since newline is also a\u001b[12;1Hseparator for the list of patterns, there is no way to match newline\u001b[K\u001b[12;1H"]
[1853.900111, "o", "\u001b[12;1H"]
