[1854.694363, "o", "\u001b[13;1H\u001b[7m-----Info: (grep)Command-line Options, 25 lines --Top-----------------------\u001b[0m\u001b[1;1HNext: Environment Variables,  Up: Invoking\u001b[K\u001b[2;1H\u001b[K\u001b[3;1H2.1 Command-line Options\u001b[K\u001b[4;1H========================\u001b[K\u001b[6;1H‘grep’ comes with a rich set of options: some from POSIX and some being\u001b[7;1HGNU extensions.  Long option names are always a GNU extension, even for\u001b[8;1H\u001b[K\u001b[8;1Hoptions that are from POSIX specifications.  Options that are specified\u001b[9;1H\u001b[K\u001b[9;1Hby POSIX, under their short names, are explicitly marked as such to\u001b[10;1H\u001b[K\u001b[10;1Hfacilitate POSIX-portable programming.  A few option names are provided\u001b[11;1H\u001b[K\u001b[11;1Hfor compatibility with older or more exotic implementations.\u001b[1;1H"]
