[1855.232232, "o", "\u001b[12;1H\u001b[13;1H\u001b[7m-----Info: (grep)Command-line Options, 25 lines --46%-----------------------\u001b[0m\u001b[1;1HGNU extensions.  Long option names are always a GNU extension, even for\u001b[2;1Hoptions that are from POSIX specifications.  Options that are specified\u001b[3;1Hby POSIX, under their short names, are explicitly marked as such to\u001b[K\u001b[4;1Hfacilitate POSIX-portable programming.  A few option names are provided\u001b[5;2Hor compatibility with older or more exotic implementations.\u001b[K\u001b[6;1H\u001b[K\u001b[7;1H* Menu:\u001b[8;1H\u001b[K\u001b[9;1H\u001b[4m* Generic Program Information\u001b[24m::\u001b[K\u001b[10;1H\u001b[4m* Matching Control\u001b[24m::\u001b[K\u001b[11;1H\u001b[4m* General Output Control\u001b[24m::\u001b[K\u001b[12;1H\u001b[1m* Output Line Prefix Control\u001b[0m::\u001b[K\u001b[12;1H"]
[1855.232336, "o", "\u001b[12;1H"]
