[1856.313462, "o", "\u001b[12;1H\u001b[13;1H\u001b[7m-----Info: (grep)Matching Control, 78 lines -- 1%---------------------------\u001b[0m\u001b[1;1Hand-line Options\u001b[K\u001b[2;1H\u001b[K\u001b[3;1H2.1.2 Matching Control\u001b[4;1H----------------------\u001b[5;1H\u001b[K\u001b[6;1H‘-e PATTERNS’\u001b[7;3H-regexp=PATTERNS’\u001b[8;1H     Use PATTERNS as one or more patterns; newlines within PATTERNS\u001b[9;6Hseparate each pattern from the next.  If this option is used\u001b[K\u001b[10;6Hmultiple times or is combined with the ‘-f’ (‘--file’) option,\u001b[11;6Hsearch for all patterns given.  Typically PATTERNS should be quoted\u001b[12;6Hwhen ‘grep’ is used in a shell command.  (‘-e’ is specified by\u001b[K\u001b[12;1H"]
