[1856.344827, "o", "\u001b[12;1H"]
[1856.376051, "o", "\u001b[12;1H\u001b[13;1H\u001b[7m-----Info: (grep)Matching Control, 78 lines -- 4%---------------------------\u001b[0m\u001b[1;1H2.1.2 Matching Control\u001b[2;1H----------------------\u001b[3;1H\u001b[K\u001b[4;1H‘-e PATTERNS’\u001b[5;3H-regexp=PATTERNS’\u001b[6;1H     Use PATTERNS as one or more patterns; newlines within PATTERNS"]
[1856.376149, "o", "\u001b[7;6Hseparate each pattern from the next.  If this option is used\u001b[K\u001b[8;6Hmultiple times or is combined with the ‘-f’ (‘--file’) option,\u001b[9;6Hsearch for all patterns given.  Typically PATTERNS should be quoted\u001b[10;6Hwhen ‘grep’ is used in a shell command.  (‘-e’ is specified by\u001b[K\u001b[11;6HPOSIX.)\u001b[K\u001b[12;1H\u001b[K\u001b[12;1H"]
[1856.37657, "o", "\u001b[12;1H"]
[1856.408485, "o", "\u001b[12;1H\u001b[13;1H\u001b[7m-----Info: (grep)Matching Control, 78 lines -- 6%---------------------------\u001b[0m\u001b[1;1H----------------------\u001b[2;1H\u001b[K\u001b[3;1H‘-e PATTERNS’\u001b[4;3H-regexp=PATTERNS’\u001b[5;1H     Use PATTERNS as one or more patterns; newlines within PATTERNS\u001b[6;6Hseparate each pattern from the next.  If this option is used\u001b[K\u001b[7;6Hmultiple times or is combined with the ‘-f’ (‘--file’) option,\u001b[8;6Hsearch for all patterns given.  Typically PATTERNS should be quoted\u001b[9;6Hwhen ‘grep’ is used in a shell command.  (‘-e’ is specified by\u001b[K\u001b[10;6HPOSIX.)\u001b[K\u001b[11;1H\u001b[K\u001b[12;1H‘-f FILE’\u001b[12;1H"]
[1856.408554, "o", "\u001b[12;1H"]
[1856.44042, "o", "\u001b[12;1H\u001b[13;1H\u001b[7m-----Info: (grep)Matching Control, 78 lines -- 7%---------------------------\u001b[0m\u001b[1;1H\u001b[K\u001b[2;1H‘-e PATTERNS’\u001b[3;3H-regexp=PATTERNS’\u001b[4;1H     Use PATTERNS as one or more patterns; newlines within PATTERNS\u001b[5;6Hseparate each pattern from the next.  If this option is used\u001b[K\u001b[6;6Hmultiple times or is combined with the ‘-f’ (‘--file’) option,\u001b[7;6Hsearch for all patterns given.  Typically PATTERNS should be quoted\u001b[8;6Hwhen ‘grep’ is used in a shell command.  (‘-e’ is specified by\u001b[K\u001b[9;6HPOSIX.)\u001b[K\u001b[10;1H\u001b[K\u001b[11;1H‘-f FILE’\u001b[12;3H-file=FILE’"]
[1856.44052, "o", "\u001b[12;1H\u001b[12;1H"]
[1856.47311, "o", "\u001b[12;1H\u001b[13;1H\u001b[7m-----Info: (grep)Matching Control, 78 lines -- 9%---------------------------\u001b[0m\u001b[1;1H‘-e PATTERNS’\u001b[2;3H-regexp=PATTERNS’\u001b[3;1H     Use PATTERNS as one or more patterns; newlines within PATTERNS\u001b[4;6Hseparate each pattern from the next.  If this option is used\u001b[K\u001b[5;6Hmultiple times or is combined with the ‘-f’ (‘--file’) option,\u001b[6;6Hsearch for all patterns given.  Typically PATTERNS should be quoted\u001b[7;6Hwhen ‘grep’ is used in a shell command.  (‘-e’ is specified by\u001b[K\u001b[8;6HPOSIX.)\u001b[K\u001b[9;1H\u001b[K"]
