[1857.009254, "o", "\u001b[12;1H\u001b[13;1H\u001b[7m-----Info: (grep)Matching Control, 78 lines --34%---------------------------\u001b[0m\u001b[1;1H‘-i’\u001b[2;3Hy’\u001b[3;3H-ignore-case’\u001b[4;1H     Ignore case distinctions in patterns and input data, so that\u001b[5;6Hcharacters that differ only in case match each other.  Although\u001b[6;6Hthis is straightforward when letters differ in case only via\u001b[K\u001b[7;6Hlowercase-uppercase pairs, the behavior is unspecified in other\u001b[8;6Hsituations.  For example, uppercase \"S\" has an unusual lowercase\u001b[9;6Hcounterpart \"ſ\" (Unicode character U+017F, LATIN SMALL LETTER LONG\u001b[10;6HS) in many locales, and it is unspecified whether this unusual\u001b[K\u001b[11;6Hcharacter matches \"S\" or \"s\" even though uppercasing it yields \"S\".\u001b[12;6HAnother example: the lowercase German letter \"ß\" (U+00DF, LATIN\u001b[K\u001b[12;1H"]
